name: Grass Drome
desc:
A kind of spongy mollusk that
likes areas with high humidity.
Produces orbal energy in its
body and uses wind arts.

name: Ice Drome
desc:
An icy cold mollusk that 
breeds in areas with lots of 
water. Creates orbal energy in 
its body and uses water arts.

name: Black Drome
desc:
A mollusk as dark as the
abyss. Produces orbal 
energy in its body and 
uses time arts.

name: Flash Drome
desc:
Mollusk that gives off light 
and stores it as a nutrient. 
Creates orbal energy in its 
body and uses space arts.

name: Magma Drome
desc:
A mollusk which draws in 
heat as a nutrient. Creates 
orbal energy in its body 
and uses fire arts.

name: Giant Drome
desc:
A giant mollusk which inhabits
Heimdallr's underground. 
Attacks all by causing the
surrounding space to vibrate.

name: Egg Snake
desc:
A reptilian monster that has
taken up living in the egg of
a large bird. Its fangs have
deadly poison inside them.

name: Rock Serpent
desc:
A serpent monster that lives
in an exceptionally hard egg
of a large bird. Its fangs can
petrify enemies.

name: Rhinocider
desc:
A monster covered by 
hardened skin. Its powerful 
charge attacks are strong 
enough to topple orbal cars.

name: Goldcider
desc:
A monster covered in a golden,
armor-like shell. Its immense
weight gives its charge
attacks incredible power.

name: Crop Muncher
desc:
A small monster that attacks
granaries. Be cautious of its
blinding sand attacks.

name: Grass Hopper
desc:
A relatively docile monster
that subsists off grass.
...Or so you think, until it
kicks sand in your face.

name: Pom
desc:
A dastardly fluff. Steals 
EP and CP from those 
who dare touch it.

name: Grass Pom
desc:
A subspecies of Pom that 
smells of fresh flowers. 
Absorbs CP and EP.

name: Shining Pom
desc:
A shining, dastardly fluff 
that absorbs CP and EP. 
Bewitches its foes using 
the bright light it emits.

name: Shining Pom
desc:
A shining, dastardly fluff 
that absorbs CP and EP. 
Bewitches its foes using 
the bright light it emits.

A shining, dastardly fluff

name: Cryon Bit
desc:
A rare infant monster. Has the
unusual habit of freezing its
prey before consuming it.

name: Shadow Spirit
desc:
An eerie spirit that lacks
a solid body. Gives those who
hear it nightmares, causing
them to lose their sanity.

name: Ghost Soul
desc:
A spirit formed from grudges.
Its ominous voice beckons all
humans who hear it to an
eternal slumber.

name: Dirty Rat
desc:
A rat monster which lives in
dark underground areas. 
Pounces on enemies unnoticed,
delaying their movement.

name: Jewel Rat
desc:
A quick-witted rat monster
with horns as hard as jewels. 
Beware its pounce attack.

name: Coco Panda
desc:
An intelligent, bipedal 
monster. Beats humans who 
pass by with a stick it made 
from a tree branch.

name: Sasa Panda
desc:
A surprisingly ferocious panda
monster. Wields a piece of
bamboo like a weapon to fight
off its enemies.

name: Green Raccoon
desc:
A small and extremely 
cautious raccoon. The stick it
always carries around was
taken from a poisonous plant.

name: Orderbelisk
desc:
A mysterious, floating pillar.
Uses powerful space arts to 
erase intruders from existence.

name: Judge Pillar
desc:
A heavenly pillar which acts
as a judge. Stops those who 
touch it from moving, and 
uses healing arts.

name: Sharkodile
desc:
An aquatic monster that lives
in underground waterways. 
Has a giant mouth that 
lets it tear through prey.

name: Great Sharkodile
desc:
An aquatic monster that rules
the capital's underground
waterways. Its jaw is strong
enough to grind bone to dust.

name: Creepy Sheep
desc:
A dynamic sheep monster. 
Capable of using an unusual
boxing style that lets it put
its foes to sleep.

name: Cherubic Gate
desc:
A floor guardian that has 
merged with a door. Fires
light rays from the jewel at 
its center to confuse foes.

name: Seraphic Gate
desc:
A glistening floor guardian.
Unleashes rays of light and
lowers foes' mobility with a
cursed roar.

name: Gordi Chief
desc:
A primate that dwells in
the forest. Its blows are so
powerful that they knock 
the recipient unconscious.

name: Gordi Schnarr
desc:
A large monkey monster 
that lives deep in the forest. 
Its powerful arms are capable 
of dealing devastating blows.

name: War Mantis
desc:
A large mantis monster. 
Wields an incredibly sharp
scythe capable of decapitating
its prey in a single strike.

name: Death Sickle
desc:
A bipedal mantis monster. Has
sharp sickles on its forelegs
and attacks humans' necks on
sight.

name: Fanged Wolf
desc:
A wolf monster that moves in
packs. Attacks prey with its
powerful fangs.

name: Greedy Wolf
desc:
A greedy wolf that came from
the mountains in search of 
food. Pursues prey endlessly,
attacking its windpipe first.

name: White Fang
desc:
A wolf monster with white
fur. Roams the highlands
and always hunts together
with its pack.

name: Mad Penguin
desc:
An avian monster that lives in
bogs and throws small fish.
It can't fly, but it doesn't
care, either.

name: Ball Bat
desc:
An exceptionally heavy bat
monster. Tackles enemies from
the air with incredible force,
knocking them back.

name: Metal Bat
desc:
A large bat monster. A steady 
diet of ore has made its fur 
as hard as steel.

name: Death Slugger
desc:
A purgatorial tank that mows
down sinners in its wake. 
Moves ceaselessly, firing its
cannon with reckless abandon.

name: Demon Rider
desc:
Tank made by alchemy, it
can pulverize anything with
its cannon. Its charge attack
slays warriors in one strike.

name: Phalanx J9
desc:
A mechanical monster. Has
immense firepower, but all
else about it is unknown.

name: Phalanx J9
desc:
An archaism designed to aid in
conquering enemy strongholds.
Fires small missiles effective
against bunched-up foes.

name: Phalanx J9
desc:
An archaism designed to aid in
conquering enemy strongholds.
Fires small missiles effective
against bunched-up foes.

name: Phalanx J9
desc:
An archaism designed to aid in
conquering enemy strongholds.
Fires small missiles effective
against bunched-up foes.

name: Fate Spinner
desc:
A menacing monster with two
sharp claws. Attacks with a
poisonous liquid that causes 
fires and hallucinations.

name: Fate Spinner
desc:
A menacing monster with two
sharp claws. Attacks with a
poisonous liquid that causes 
fires and hallucinations.

name: Acerbic Tomartian
desc:
A living acerbic tomato, born
from a sudden mutation. Its
juices are bitter enough to
make you go insane.

name: Hellish Tomartian
desc:
A mutation of a mutation,
with an obscenely hellish
level of bitterness.

name: Thunder Quaker
desc:
An ancient fish capable of
producing electricity in its
body. Can char foes within
a wide area.

name: Wandering Armor
desc:
A suit of armor from the
Middle Ages that gained the
ability to move in a strange
environment. Very sturdy.

name: Wandering Sword
desc:
A sword from the Middle Ages
capable of fighting by itself.
Can take the life of an
intruder in a single blow.

name: Nosferatu
desc:
An immortal king from ancient
legends with authority over
souls. Takes the souls of the
innocent and devours them.

name: NT-I
desc:
A self-detonating mine set 
by C. Causes a large-scale
explosion.

name: Cursed Sculpture
desc:
A devil said to have existed
since the Dark Ages. With its
spread wings, it is a symbol
of fear.

name: Pit Demon
desc:
A devil's minion, mentioned in
the Testaments. Charms foes
with waves, luring them into
an eternal slumber.

name: Flying Feline
desc:
A winged feline monster. 
Relentlessly pursues its
prey, attacking with kicks
from above.

name: White Feline
desc:
A subspecies of flying feline
with white fur. Once raised 
as a pet by a noble, but was
abandoned and turned feral.

name: Dastardly Amalgam
desc:
A mollusk monster that covers
itself with broken stones and
rocks for protection.

name: Frost Biter
desc:
A mollusk monster covered
with very cold minerals. All
who touch it turn to ice.

name: Coin Beetle
desc:
A golden-colored beetle. Its 
carapace is hard like a coin.

name: Metal Beetle
desc:
A beetle with a metallic
shell. Was once frequently
dug up when people mistook 
them for actual ore.

name: Attack Dog
desc:
A canine monster with a 
violent temperament. Known
for the spines covering much
of its body.

name: Dark Canine
desc:
A nocturnal canine monster
that made its way into the
castle. Aggressive, with
poison in its claws.

name: Attack Dog G
desc:
The name given to especially
large attack dogs. They are
even more dangerous than
the regular kind.

name: Blade Horn
desc:
A large insect monster with a
horn resembling a blade. Uses
it to forcefully shatter foes.

name: Blue Horn
desc:
A beetle covered with a hard
shell. Knocks prey unconscious
with its powerful horn.

name: Blade Pincer
desc:
An arthropod monster with a 
pair of sharp pincers and a 
hard shell. Loathed by people
for munching on crops.

name: Steel Ladybug
desc:
A beetle monster with a shell
of steel. Its sharp claws can
snap trees in half.

name: Claydoll
desc:
An ancient humanoid that
roams the old schoolhouse's
underground area, repelling
intruders.

name: Iglute Garmr
desc:
A stone gargoyle spoken of in
Erebonian legends. Repels
intruders with powerful
gusts of wind.

name: Iglute Garmr
desc:
A stone gargoyle spoken of in
Erebonian legends. Its sturdy
body repels physical attacks.

name: Iglute GarmrEVNeck
desc:
Guardian of the ruins, 
designed to repel intruders.
Physical attacks aren't very
effective against it.

name: Obsidian Garmr
desc:
A jet-black stone guardian.
Its powerful tail strikes are
capable of forcing anything
aside.

name: Mantrap
desc:
A plant-like monster that
roams highways. Draws 
impurities from below the
ground and attacks with them.

name: Mad Weed
desc:
A mysterious plant said to
bloom in the abyss. Produces
a miasma that lowers foes'
vitality significantly.

name: Venus Mantrap
desc:
A three-headed plant monster.
Stores impurities within its
body, which it sprays at its
enemies.

name: Pit Cerberus
desc:
A plant-like monster that
roams the darkness. Blows a
deadly miasma that instantly
takes away foes' vision.

name: Ol-Gadia
desc:
A headless knight that 
emerged from within the 
red door. It seems to be 
designed to serve as a 'trial.'

name: Ol-Gadia
desc:
A headless knight that 
emerged from within the 
red door. It seems to be 
designed to serve as a 'trial.'

name: Og-Jior
desc:
Keeper of an ancient ruin,
it forcibly repels intruders. 
Uses its giant iron sword 
to pulverize its foes.

name: Stealth Turtle
desc:
A ferocious turtle monster.
Hides itself in the shadows
of bushes, attacking prey 
as it passes by.

name: Zaurtoise
desc:
A turtle monster with a hard
shell. It being on the slow
side hasn't stopped it from
prospering in the highlands.

name: Elvavria
desc:
An archaism from the Middle
Ages, armed with numerous
weapons. Paralyzes foes with
wide-reaching beams.

name: Kazakh Doven B
desc:
A military monster trained 
by the provincial army. 
Coordinates with allies to be
sure their prey can't escape.

name: Kazakh Doven R
desc:
A military monster used by the
provincial army. Rouses allies
with a howl, working with
them to deal great damage.

name: Kazakh Doven G
desc:
A military monster released by
the Imperial Liberation Front.
Powerful enough to break 
through thick armor.

name: Zesvia
desc:
A spider monster that has
existed since antiquity. 
Feared as the cause of 
innumerable plagues.

name: Ginosha-Zanak
desc:
Sealed away as an 'evil djinn'
in ancient times. Binds prey 
with very hard threads for its
children to devour.

name: Deathcargot
desc:
A land-dwelling mollusk 
monster with a hard shell. 
Steals life from its prey then
finishes it with water arts.

name: Time Snail
desc:
A mollusk monster with a
hard shell. Stops prey in 
its tracks with time arts 
and slowly absorbs nutrients.

name: Evil Crow
desc:
An unpleasant bird with a 
distinctive large beak. Has a
ferocious appetite, swallowing
small creatures whole.

name: Scavenger Crow
desc:
A strange kind of bird that
lives underground. Spends 
much of its time scouring 
waterways for food.

name: Ripper Squirrel
desc:
An adorable but deadly 
monster with a sharp tail. 
Its spin attack is incredibly 
dangerous.

name: King Dragonfly
desc:
A large dragonfly monster 
that flies around near fields. 
Expels poisonous liquids 
from an organ in its body.

name: Crimson Dragonfly
desc:
A large, red dragonfly 
monster. Sprays lethal 
poison, mandating 
caution when fighting one.

name: Scary Dinosaur
desc:
A ferocious lizard monster.
Releases sound waves by
vibrating its dorsal fin, then
crushes prey with its teeth.

name: Turtle Bug
desc:
An arthropod monster with a 
hard shell. Stores high
pressure gas in its body, 
which it uses to attack foes.

name: Platinum Bug
desc:
An arthropod with a carapace 
as hard as stone. Secretes a
highly unpleasant smelling
fluid, making enemies faint.

name: Hornteater
desc:
A monster with a hard carapace
over its back. Impales prey
with its horns, then slowly 
eats it with its long tongue.

name: Brutal Buffa
desc:
A buffalo monster that is
always on the move across 
the highlands. Mostly docile,
but fiercely territorial.

name: Anteater
desc:
An infant Hornteater. When it
becomes older, it grows horns
and a hard carapace over its
back.

name: Brutal Infant
desc:
An infant buffalo monster. 
Gains the ability to move
freely within hours of birth,
joining the herd on its own.

name: Infant Drango
desc:
A monster that resembles the
dragons in legend. Small in
size, but capable of turning
a wide area to ash.

name: Zoro-Agruga
desc:
A dragon-like fiend from the
Dark Ages made of bone. Sprays
dark breath and has the power
to shake space itself.

name: Zwordar
desc:
A ferocious bird of prey.
Pulls prey upwards with a
whirlwind, and then catches
it with its sharp talons.

name: Great Grouse
desc:
A giant avian monster that
lives in mountainous regions.
Creates whirlwinds which tear
living things to shreds.

name: Zwordar
desc:
A ferocious bird of prey.
Pulls prey upwards with a
whirlwind, and then catches
it with its sharp talons.

name: Vampiric Thorn
desc:
A strange plant monster. 
Usually lurks underground,
draining its prey of every
last drop of blood.

name: Greedy Reaper
desc:
A worm monster that lurks
underground. Its body is
covered in tough armor, and
it drains HP from its prey.

name: Hydra
desc:
A serpent monster with many
heads, each acting separately.
Each head competes to feast on
prey, eating even the bones.

name: Thunder Hydra
desc:
A serpent fiend with many
heads. Sprays lightning 
breath by generating 
electricity in its body.

name: Thunder Loach
desc:
An infant fish capable of
producing electricity with its
feelers. It may be young, but
it is still deadly.

name: Grunoja
desc:
Ruler of Lunaria Nature Park,
it attacks those who enter
its territory. Smashes all 
who oppose it to pieces.

name: Crocodark
desc:
An amphibian monster that 
lives near water. Its appetite
is ferocious, and its jaw is
strong enough to pierce steel.

name: Hippogriff
desc:
A large bird that hunts on
the highlands. Its talons
contain deadly poison, and it
can spew burning-hot breath.

name: Roc
desc:
A cunning, ferocious bird 
that hunts on the mountain
path. Freezes its prey before 
carrying it back to its nest.

name: Tri-Attacker R2
desc:
A patrol archaism released by
the Imperial Liberation Front.
Very mobile, and capable of
machine gun and missile fire.

name: Tri-Attacker HG
desc:
A patrol archaism released by
the Imperial Liberation Front.
Reduces foes' movement and
defense with electromagnetism.

name: Tri-Attacker R2
desc:
A patrol archaism released by
the Imperial Liberation Front.
Very mobile, and capable of
machine gun and missile fire.

name: Tri-Attacker HG
desc:
A patrol archaism released by
the Imperial Liberation Front.
Reduces foes' movement and
defense with electromagnetism.

name: Tri-Attacker R2
desc:
A patrol archaism released by
the Imperial Liberation Front.
Very mobile, and capable of
machine gun and missile fire.

name: Tri-Attacker HG
desc:
A patrol archaism released by
the Imperial Liberation Front.
Reduces foes' movement and
defense with electromagnetism.

name: Unsurtr
desc:
A giant beast with a body
covered in ice. Freezes
all with frigid blizzards.

name: Durgnessa
desc:
A massive, mountain-like
fiend. Being trampled by
its immense weight is enough
to crush anything.

name: Dancing Owl
desc:
Avian monster with beautiful
wings. Those who witness its
strange dance suffer various
status abnormalities.

name: Gespard
desc:
An assault archaism. Can deal
with foes in a wide area due
to its elastic arms and 
devastating main cannon.

name: Gespard G
desc:
An assault archaism made 
by Ouroboros. Charges 
its enemies and unleashes 
wide reaching destruction.

name: Moon Mole
desc:
A mole monster that lives 
in the sealed mine shaft. 
Its claws are ideal both for 
digging and cutting prey.

name: Jelly Shroom
desc:
A massively swollen fungus.
Paralyzes organisms that
approach it and slowly feeds
on their nutrients.

name: Rose Shroom
desc:
A mollusk formed from several
pink spores. Possesses a 
powerful neurotoxin. Touching
it causes paralysis.

name: Gold Fungus
desc:
A spore monster that became 
massively enlarged due to 
eating high-quality ore. The 
reason the shaft was closed.

name: Bomb Spider
desc:
An arthropod monster that eats
wreckage left by explosions. 
Detonates the poison sac on 
its back if it senses danger.

name: Lantern Spider
desc:
An arthropod monster with an
air sac that gives off a pale
light on its back. This sac
contains a poisonous liquid.

name: Ostrich
desc:
A strange bird that races
around on non-paved 
plains. Its breath allows 
it to petrify its prey.

name: Stony Croaker
desc:
A large, frog-like monster with
skin like rock. Draws in prey
with its long tongue and 
restrains it with mucus.

name: Rocky Croaker
desc:
A large, frog-like monster. 
Its skin is as hard as iron,
due to all the stones it eats.

name: Zephyranthes
desc:
A large archaism designed for
defending strongholds. Reduces
enemy numbers with lasers and
immense firepower.

name: G-Zephyranthes
desc:
A large, golden archaism. 
Supports C with powerful 
laser beams and wide-range
shockwaves.

name: B-Zephyranthes
desc:
A large archaism designed 
for defending strongholds. 
This improved blue model 
has incredible firepower.

name: R-Zephyranthes
desc:
A red archaism strengthened
to support the ILF's leaders.
Even more powerful and deadly
than standard models.

name: Zephyranthes
desc:
A large archaism designed for
defending strongholds. Reduces
enemy numbers with lasers and
immense firepower.

name: Combat Shell
desc:
A combat dummy that didn't 
get used in the game.
Poor Combat Shell-kun...
your day will come, eventually.

name: Combat Shell
desc:
A combat dummy set up 
for practical exams. Feels 
strange to the touch, and 
fights as programmed.

name: Combat Shell
desc:
A combat dummy that operates
by some unknown means. Its
change of form allows it to
use more powerful attacks.

name: Combat Shell
desc:
A combat dummy made of a 
mysterious metal. Has high
attack and defense power 
to simulate real battle.

name: Combat Shell
desc:
A combat dummy that operates
by some unknown means. Its
change of form allows it to
use more powerful attacks.

name: Winged Snake
desc:
A winged snake that flies
around on the Nord Highlands.
The people of Nord fear the
poison in its fangs.

name: Diving Ananta
desc:
A serpent monster containing
deadly poison. Plunges its
fangs into its prey from the
air using its bat-like wings.

name: Stone Golem
desc:
A golem created from stone
which appears in Erebonian
legends. Can cause earthquakes
by stamping on the ground.

name: Steel Golem
desc:
A magical golem born by
giving life to steel. Causes 
powerful earthquakes at will.

name: Dissolution Slug
desc:
A mollusk monster with
countless feelers. Uses 
acid stored in its body to 
dissolve and devour its prey.

name: Diglem
desc:
A stone statue allowed to move
because of the strange force
active in the quarry. Lowers
foes' abilities with beams.

name: Star Lambda
desc:
A stone statue granted life by
a mysterious power. Lowers 
the abilities of its foes with
cursed beams of light.

name: Stone Stalker
desc:
A four-legged stone creature.
When it sees an enemy, it
approaches them, then attacks
with its weight from above.

name: Ghoul Frog
desc:
A mass of dead monsters. 
Has exceptional regenerative
abilities.

name: Polyjelly
desc:
A floating spore creature from
another world. Those who touch
it turn to stone.

name: Hell Rabbit
desc:
A monster said to have come
from the underworld. Those
pierced by its spines are 
believed to lose their souls.

name: Ramon
desc:
A fiend with black fur, said
to be a servant of Gehenna.
Appears before those who have
little time left to live.

name: Glaceron
desc:
A large turtle with a stone-
like carapace. Sprays rocks
from its back to repel foes.

name: Lunar Bee
desc:
A bee-like fiend capable
of crossing dimensions. Its
highly lethal poison makes it
incredibly dangerous.

name: Purple Ooze
desc:
A strange lifeform from
another world. Can drain large
amounts of HP, EP, and CP,
making it a difficult foe.

name: Hinomikoto
desc:
A beast with boiling hot 
blood. Deified by some.
Charges foes with its burning
horns and uses fire arts.

name: Rup Kamuy
desc:
A beast that roams places
that are extremely cold. Said
to rule over ice and snow. Its
antlers freeze foes on contact.

name: Minos Demon
desc:
A powerful, two-horned, evil
creature. Obscures foes' 
vision with dark breath and
then pulverizes them.

name: Minos Demon
desc:
A powerful, two-horned, evil
creature. Obscures foes' 
vision with dark breath and
then pulverizes them.

name: Surtr
desc:
A demi-human fiend that
governs fire. Its sword is
made of fire so hot, it can
boil steel.

name: Ashen Fragment
desc:
Fragment of the Ashen Power.
Lulls would-be intruders of
the realm to sleep, where they
experience nightmares.

name: Loa Erebonius
desc:
A shadow of the Great Power
which appeared on the 
Otherworldly Battlefield.
Carries out the Final Trial.

name: Patrick
desc:
Third son of Marquis Hyarms.
Exceptionally skilled with a
sword thanks to his high-
quality education.

name: C
desc:
A mysterious masked man who
leads the terrorists. Wields
a double saber with immense
skill, using varied attacks.

name: C
desc:
A mysterious masked man who 
leads the Imperial Liberation
Front. Wields a double saber
with immense skill.

name: G (Gideon)
desc:
A man belonging to an unknown
organization who hired the
